%description:
Deterministic MLDv2 router/querier behavior test (RFC 3810 §7).

Tests the MLDv2 router (querier) side with a fixed RNG seed and short timers so the
behaviors are observable within a 15s simulation. Membership is driven by a real app
(UdpSink with multicastGroup), the production path. Same scenario as
MLD_router_basic.test, but with **.ipv6.mld.typename="Mldv2".

RTRv2-01 (General Query on startup):
  The router has multicastForwarding=true (set at node level so NetworkLayerNodeBase
  propagates it to the routing table). configureInterface() starts the querier on each
  multicast-capable interface and sends the first General Query immediately, scheduling
  the next at startupQueryInterval. The "Sending General Query on interface ..." EV_INFO
  marker is asserted.

RTRv2-02 (listener recorded on Report):
  host1 runs UdpSink with multicastGroup="ff0e::1:2:3" (any-source join). The socket
  join at t=0 fires the membership change -> the host sends a State-Change Report
  (TO_EX). The router receives it ("Received Mldv2 Multicast Listener Report ..."),
  finds the record for ff0e::1:2:3, and -- because TO_EX moves the router group to
  EXCLUDE filter mode with Group Timer = GMI -- records the group's forwarding state.
  The "Found a record for group 'ff0e::1:2:3'" and TO_EX-reception markers are asserted.

RTRv2-03 (Multicast-Address-Specific Query after a leave):
  host1's UdpSink has stopTime=5s. The socket close fires the EXCLUDE()->INCLUDE()
  membership change, so the host sends a CHANGE_TO_INCLUDE_MODE (TO_IN, empty source
  list) Report. The router is in EXCLUDE filter mode for the group, so on receiving the
  TO_IN it follows RFC 3810 §7.4 "Reception of a TO_IN" for the EXCLUDE case and sends a
  Multicast-Address-Specific Query Q(G) for ff0e::1:2:3. That marker is asserted.

RTRv2-04 (Multicast-Address-Specific Query retransmission, RFC 3810 §7.6.3):
  The Query is sent [Last Listener Query Count] (=lastMemberQueryCount=2) times in
  total, lastMemberQueryInterval (=1s) apart: the initial send plus one
  retransmission. The "Retransmitting Multicast-Address-Specific Query ..." marker is
  asserted.

HOST-ONLY NEGATIVE (single-querier proof):
  host1 has multicastForwarding=false (the default); only the router runs the querier
  path. A %postrun-command extracts any "Sending ... Query" lines emitted by host1's MLD
  module and a %not-contains asserts the list is empty.

Network: host1 (StandardHost6) and router (Router6) on a shared EthernetHub.
Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator assigns addresses. Both nodes have hasMld=true and
mld.typename="Mldv2". DAD disabled; RNG seed pinned.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetHub;
import inet.node.ipv6.Router6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network Mldv2RouterBasicNetwork
{
    types:
        channel ethline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
        host1: StandardHost6;
        router: Router6;
        hub: EthernetHub;
    connections:
        host1.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        router.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../src
network = Mldv2RouterBasicNetwork
sim-time-limit = 15s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "

# Fix RNG seed for deterministic behavior of uniform(0, maxRespDelay) in the host timer
seed-set = 0

eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

# Enable MLDv2 on all nodes so they can receive inbound Reports
**.ipv6.hasMld = true
**.ipv6.mld.typename = "Mldv2"
# Disable DAD for fast startup
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 10

# RTRv2-01: activate the real querier ONLY on the router (node-level multicastForwarding).
**.router.multicastForwarding = true

# RTRv2-01 timers: shorten query intervals for a fast deterministic run.
**.router.ipv6.mld.startupQueryInterval = 1s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryInterval = 5s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryResponseInterval = 1s
# RTRv2-03 last-member timers
**.router.ipv6.mld.lastMemberQueryInterval = 1s
**.router.ipv6.mld.lastMemberQueryCount = 2

# RTRv2-02: host1 joins ff0e::1:2:3 via UdpSink (fires the membership change -> State-Change Report).
**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host1.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1:2:3"
# RTRv2-03: host1 leaves at t=5s via socket close (fires the EXCLUDE()->INCLUDE() change -> TO_IN).
**.host1.app[0].stopTime = 5s

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTRv2-01: router sends the first General Query on startup
%contains: stdout
Mldv2RouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Sending General Query on interface 'eth0', and scheduling next Query

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTRv2-02: router receives host1's State-Change Report
%contains: stdout
Mldv2RouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Received Mldv2 Multicast Listener Report on interface 'eth0'.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTRv2-02: router finds the record for ff0e::1:2:3
%contains: stdout
Mldv2RouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Found a record for group 'ff0e::1:2:3'.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTRv2-02: the join is a TO_EX (any-source/EXCLUDE) record, received and processed by the router
%contains: stdout
Mldv2RouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Received TO_EX() report.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTRv2-03: on the leave (TO_IN while in EXCLUDE mode) the router sends a Multicast-Address-Specific Query
%contains: stdout
Mldv2RouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Sending Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group 'ff0e::1:2:3' on interface 'eth0'.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTRv2-04: the Multicast-Address-Specific Query is retransmitted lastMemberQueryCount-1 times (RFC 3810 7.6.3)
%contains: stdout
Mldv2RouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Retransmitting Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group 'ff0e::1:2:3' on interface 'eth0'

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-ONLY NEGATIVE (single-querier proof): host1 has multicastForwarding=false and must
%# NEVER send any Query. Extract all host1 Query-sending lines; the resulting file must be empty.
%postrun-command: grep -E "Mldv2RouterBasicNetwork\.host1\.ipv6\.mld: Sending (General|Multicast-Address-Specific|Multicast-Address-and-Source-Specific) Query" test.out > host1_query.out || true
%not-contains: host1_query.out
Query

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Undisposed-object guard
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
